INSERT INTO `modules` VALUES (1,'Analysing Fiction',1,'Fiction is usually made up by the writer. Fiction texts could be based on the writer’s own life experiences or come from their imagination (or be a mixture of the two)','2022-04-06 11:46:28','2022-04-06 11:46:28'),(2,'Analysing Non-Fiction',1,'Exploring the types, audience, purpose and structure of non-fiction texts','2022-04-06 11:46:28','2022-04-06 11:46:28'),(3,'Comparing Texts',1,'Comparing involves directly linking texts through their similarities and differences. It is important to move equally between the two texts, and write about them together, not separately.','2022-04-06 11:46:28','2022-04-06 11:46:28'),(4,'Writing',1,'How to write the different kinds of text types including purpose, form, planning and organising ideas','2022-04-06 11:46:28','2022-04-06 11:46:28'),(5,'Spelling, Punctuation and Grammar',1,'An in-depth look at how spelling, punctuation and grammar affects your writing','2022-04-06 11:46:28','2022-04-06 11:46:28'),(6,'Spoken Language',1,'Exploring the factors that effect your spoken language such as personal presence, voice, responding and interacting','2022-04-06 11:46:28','2022-04-06 11:46:28'),(7,'Shakespeare',2,'In this module we will cover many of Shakespeare\'s important works','2022-04-06 11:46:28','2022-04-06 11:46:28'),(8,'Cell Biology',5,'A look at the workings and make up of cells such as structure and cell division','2022-04-06 11:46:28','2022-04-06 11:46:28'),(9,'Organisation',5,'In-depth look at the organisation of the different types of cells','2022-04-06 11:46:28','2022-04-06 11:46:28'),(10,'Infection and Response',5,'Exploring diseases, how they spread and how they might be treated or cured','2022-04-06 11:46:28','2022-04-06 11:46:28'),(11,'Bioenergetics',5,'Discovering the mechanisms behind energy creation in plants and organisms','2022-04-06 11:46:28','2022-04-06 11:46:28'),(12,'Homeostasis and Response',5,'Exploring the human nervous and endocrine systems, hormones, homeostasis and plant hormones','2022-04-06 11:46:28','2022-04-06 11:46:28'),(13,'Inheritance and Evolution',5,'Exploring the mechanics of inheritance through the genome and genes, genetic inheritance, variation and evolution','2022-04-06 11:46:28','2022-04-06 11:46:28'),(14,'Ecology',5,'The study of the relationships between living organisms, including humans, and their physical environment; it seeks to understand the vital connections between plants and animals and the world around them.','2022-04-06 11:46:28','2022-04-06 11:46:28'),(15,'Practical Skills',5,'Scientific investigations have several stages - planning, collecting data, analysing data and evaluation. It is important to understand how to carry out each stage of the investigation.','2022-04-06 11:46:28','2022-04-06 11:46:28'),(16,'Atomic Structure',6,'Exploring diseases, how they spread and how they might be treated or cured','2022-04-06 11:46:28','2022-04-06 11:46:28'),(17,'Properties of Matter',6,'Looking at bonding, structure, the 3 states of matter, compounds and metals and alloys','2022-04-06 11:46:28','2022-04-06 11:46:28'),(18,'Quantitative Chemistry',6,'The calculations involved in chemistry to obtain masses, concentration of solutions and percentage yield','2022-04-06 11:46:28','2022-04-06 11:46:28'),(19,'Chemical Changes',6,'Chemical changes occur when a substance combines with another to form a new substance, called chemical synthesis or, alternatively, chemical decomposition into two or more different substances.','2022-04-06 11:46:28','2022-04-06 11:46:28'),(20,'Energy Exchanges',6,'Energy exchanges occur in exothermic and endothermic reactions as well as in chemical cells such as batteries','2022-04-06 11:46:28','2022-04-06 11:46:28'),(21,'Areas of Study',8,'Exploring the mediums of art such as ceramics, drawing and painting','2022-04-06 11:46:28','2022-04-06 11:46:28'),(22,'Creative Process',8,'A look at the process involved in creating art such as inspiration, responding to stimuli, develo