INSERT INTO `sub_modules` VALUES (1,'Fiction Text Types',1,'Fiction is usually made up by the writer. Fiction texts could be based on the writer’s own life experiences or come from their imagination (or be a mixture of the two).','2022-04-06 11:46:28','2022-04-06 11:46:28'),(2,'Setting',1,'The setting of a text includes the location and time when events take place. Setting can play a crucial part in establishing atmosphere and reflecting themes and character within a text.','2022-04-06 11:46:28','2022-04-06 11:46:28'),(3,'Themes',1,'Themes are the main ideas or meaning that run through a text and may be shown directly or indirectly. When working out themes it helps to look closely at the language choice, setting and characters.','2022-04-06 11:46:28','2022-04-06 11:46:28'),(4,'Characterisation and narrative voice',1,'Characterisation is when a writer creates fictional characters for a narrative.','2022-04-06 11:46:28','2022-04-06 11:46:28'),(5,'Language and structure',1,'Language (words and phrases) and structure (the order of ideas in a text) are the methods used by writers to create effective characters, setting, narratives and themes.','2022-04-06 11:46:28','2022-04-06 11:46:28'),(6,'Annotating texts',1,'Annotating is when you add notes or comments to a text; this could also include underlining or circling individual words or phrases.','2022-04-06 11:46:28','2022-04-06 11:46:28'),(7,'Responding to a fiction text',1,'When responding to a fiction text you will be asked to focus on a particular area, picking out specific details or responding more fully with a close analysis.','2022-04-06 11:46:28','2022-04-06 11:46:28'),(15,'Ceramics',21,'Ceramics is the art of making three dimensional objects from clay. The choice of clay and the techniques used to shape, decorate, glaze and fire it will all have an impact on the final piece.','2022-04-28 21:00:37','2022-04-28 21:00:37'),(16,'Drawing',21,'Artists can experiment with a variety of techniques, materials and media when drawing in order to develop and communicate ideas.','2022-04-28 21:00:50','2022-04-28 21:00:50'),(17,'Painting',21,'Artists can experiment with paints, techniques and painting styles to give character to the subject of a painting and evoke different emotions from the viewer.','2022-04-28 21:01:06','2022-04-28 21:01:06'),(18,'Photography',21,'Photography is the art of capturing and manipulating images. Photographers can use film and digital cameras as well as camera-less photography to create images.','2022-04-28 21:01:21','2022-04-28 21:01:21'),(19,'Printing',21,'Printing is the process of making images that can be transferred onto other surfaces. It can be used to make one or more identical images or to create repeating patterns on papers and textiles.','2022-04-28 21:01:35','2022-04-28 21:01:35'),(20,'Finding inspiration',22,'Artists and designers look for inspiration to use as a starting point for their creative projects. Many artists and designers find inspiration in the work of others.','2022-04-28 21:21:24','2022-04-28 21:21:24'),(21,'Responding to stimuli',22,'Artists and designers find stimuli in the world around them or research a particular topic to find stimuli. They use this material to help them generate a personal creative response in their work.','2022-04-28 21:21:39','2022-04-28 21:21:39'),(22,'Analytical drawing',22,'Artists use analytical drawing techniques to explore and record their subject matter. Designers also often use analytical drawing to investigate the visual qualities of their sources of inspiration.','2022-04-28 21:21:50','2022-04-28 21:21:50'),(23,'Developing ideas',22,'Developing ideas is part of the creative process for artists and designers. By exploring and refining ideas, effective decisions can be made about the final piece of artwork or design solution.','2022-04-28 21:22:02','2022-04-28 21:22:02'),(24,'Creating a design brief',22,'Designers use a brief to give them guidance and focus. A brief helps define the design problem and gives details on important considerations and constraints.','2022-04-28 21:22:13','2022-04-28 21:22:13'),(25,'Experimenting with materials',22,'Artists and designers use a variety of materials and techniques for different purposes and to create different effects.','2022-04-28 21:22:38','2022-04-28 21:22:38'),(26,'Recording and observing',22,'Recording your ideas, observations and insights will help your creative process. You can do this visually, through writing or by using other media.','2022-04-28 21:22:52','2022-04-28 21:22:52'),(27,'Annotating your work',22,'Annotation means writing key information alongside your work. It can help to record your thoughts, keep your development on track and let others know what you have done and why.','2022-04-28 21:23:10','2022-04-28 21:23:10'),(28,'Analysing and evaluating',22,'Artists and designers often record ideas they have for artworks and designs. They will note down observations as they go so they can analyse and evaluate the effectiveness of the work produced','2022-04-28 21:23:23','2022-04-28 21:23:23'),(29,'Presenting your intentions',22,'To effectively present your project you need to show how you have developed ideas, refined your work, recorded your process and created a personal and meaningful response.','2022-04-28 21:23:53','2022-04-28 21:23:53'),(31,'Line',23,'Lines are used by artists and designers to describe objects, add detail or create expression. Lines define an artwork and reveal the artist’s techniques.','2022-04-28 21:25:27','2022-04-28 21:25:27'),(32,'Colour',23,'Choices of colour and the relationships between colours have a huge influence on how a piece or art or design looks and feels and the emotions it provokes.','2022-04-28 21:25:37','2022-04-28 21:25:37'),(33,'Tone',23,'Tone means how light or dark something is. The tones artists and designers use and the contrast between them can create very different moods and visual effects.','2022-04-28 21:25:48','2022-04-28 21:25:48'),(34,'Shape',23,'Shapes are two-dimensional. Positive shapes represent solid objects and negative shapes show the surrounding space. Geometric shapes are perfect and regular. Organic shapes are irregular and natural.','2022-04-28 21:25:59','2022-04-28 21:25:59'),(35,'Form',23,'Form refers to three dimensional objects. While shapes have two dimensions (height and width), forms have three dimensions (height, width and depth).','2022-04-28 21:26:09','2022-04-28 21:26:09'),(36,'Space',23,'Three-dimensional work creates real space. Two-dimensional works can create implied space using artistic technique. Objects take up positive space, while negative space is the empty space around them.','2022-04-28 21:26:23','2022-04-28 21:26:23'),(37,'Texture',23,'Artists and designers can use actual texture in their work or they can suggest how something feels using techniques that imply texture.','2022-04-28 21:26:50','2022-04-28 21:26:50'),(38,'Pattern',23,'A pattern is a design in which lines, shapes, forms or colours are repeated. The part that is repeated is called a motif. Patterns can be regular or irregular.','2022-04-28 21:26:59','2022-04-28 21:26:59'),(39,'Balance',24,'The arrangement of elements in a composition can create balance or imbalance. Three key ways to create balance are through symmetry, asymmetry and radial symmetry.','2022-04-28 21:27:16','2022-04-28 21:27:16'),(40,'Emphasis',24,'Emphasis is what makes part of a composition stand out. Artists and designers can emphasise something in various ways which include using its position, using converging lines, or by making it unusual.','2022-04-28 21:27:25','2022-04-28 21:27:25'),(41,'Proportion',24,'Proportion describes the relationship between the dimensions of different elements and an overall composition. Scale refers to an artwork’s size and how parts of a composition relate to each other.','2022-04-28 21:27:35','2022-04-28 21:27:35'),(42,'Unity',24,'Unity refers to how different elements of an artwork or design work come together and create a sense of wholeness. It can be achieved through proximity, simplicity, repetition and continuation.','2022-04-28 21:27:48','2022-04-28 21:27:48'),(43,'Variety',24,'Variety refers to how artists and designers add complexity to their work using visual elements. Contrast, difference and change, and elaboration all add visual interest to an artist’s work.','2022-04-28 21:28:05','2022-04-28 21:28:05'),(44,'Rhythm',24,'Rhythm refers to how elements are repeated or how they change and develop. Rhythm can be described as either regular, flowing or progressive.','2022-04-28 21:28:24','2022-04-28 21:28:24'),(45,'Cell structure',8,'Organisms are made up of cells. Most organisms are multicellular and have cells that are specialised to do a particular job. Microscopes are needed to study cells in detail.','2022-04-28 21:29:06','2022-04-28 21:29:06'),(46,'Cell division',8,'Chromosomes carry genetic information in a molecule called DNA. A type of cell division called mitosis ensures that when a cell divides each new cell produced has the same genetic information.','2022-04-28 21:29:15','2022-04-28 21:29:15'),(47,'Transport in cells',8,'For an organism to function, substances must move into and out of cells. Three processes contribute to this movement – diffusion, osmosis and active transport.','2022-04-28 21:29:29','2022-04-28 21:29:29'),(48,'Animal organisation - gaseous exchange',9,'Most animals and plants consist of different types of cells organised as tissues, organs and systems. The human respiratory system is a body system adapted for efficient gas exchange.','2022-04-28 21:30:11','2022-04-28 21:30:11'),(49,'Animal organisation - digestion',9,'The major nutrients required for a healthy diet are carbohydrates, proteins and lipids. The digestive system breaks down large molecules of food, which are then absorbed into the bloodstream.','2022-04-28 21:32:05','2022-04-28 21:32:05'),(50,'Animal organisation - transport systems',9,'Multicellular organisms require transport systems to supply their cells and remove waste products. In humans, one of the functions of the circulatory system is to transport substances.','2022-04-28 21:33:16','2022-04-28 21:33:16'),(51,'Plant organisation',9,'Plant cells, tissues and organs are adapted to their functions. The stem, root and leaves form an organ system that transports substances into, around and out of a plant.','2022-04-28 21:33:33','2022-04-28 21:33:33'),(52,'Non-communicable diseases',9,'Health is the state of physical and mental well-being. Factors work together and affect physical and mental health. A disease is a disorder that affects an organism\'s body, organs, tissues or cells.','2022-04-28 21:33:43','2022-04-28 21:33:43'),(53,'Communicable diseases',10,'Pathogens are disease-causing viruses, bacteria, fungi or protists, which can infect animals and plants. Humans have an immune system, which can defend them from pathogens.','2022-04-28 21:34:07','2022-04-28 21:34:07'),(54,'Treating, curing and preventing disease',10,'Some diseases can be treated with antibiotics. Vaccinations allow protection against specific diseases, but the level of protection depends on the amount of people vaccinated.','2022-04-28 21:34:18','2022-04-28 21:34:18'),(55,'Monoclonal antibodies - Higher',10,'Monoclonal antibodies are identical copies of one type of antibody.','2022-04-28 21:34:31','2022-04-28 21:34:31'),(56,'Plant disease',10,'Pathogens are disease-causing viruses, bacteria, fungi or protists which attack plants as well as animals. Plants have physical and chemical defences against pathogens.','2022-04-28 21:34:40','2022-04-28 21:34:40'),(57,'Photosynthesis',11,'Plants make their own food using photosynthesis. The food that plants produce is important, not only for the plants themselves, but for the other organisms that feed on the plants.','2022-04-28 21:34:55','2022-04-28 21:34:55'),(58,'Respiration',11,'All organisms respire in order to release energy to fuel their living processes. The respiration can be aerobic, which uses glucose and oxygen, or anaerobic which uses only glucose.','2022-04-28 21:35:06','2022-04-28 21:35:06'),(59,'Coordination & Control - Nervous System',12,'The nervous system enables humans to react to their surroundings and to coordinate their behaviour. It comprises millions of neurones and uses electrical impulses to communicate very quickly.','2022-04-28 21:36:00','2022-04-28 21:36:00'),(60,'Coordination & control - Endocrine',12,'The endocrine system secretes hormones into the bloodstream from glands throughout the body. Hormones produce an effect on specific target organs in the body.','2022-04-28 21:37:24','2022-04-28 21:37:24'),(61,'Hormones in human reproduction',12,'Hormones are secreted by glands in the endocrine system. During puberty, hormones create changes in physical and emotional characteristics.','2022-04-28 21:37:38','2022-04-28 21:37:38'),(62,'Homeostasis in humans',12,'Homeostasis is the regulation of internal conditions inside cells or organisms, to create the optimum conditions for biological function.','2022-04-28 21:37:47','2022-04-28 21:37:47'),(63,'Plant hormones',12,'Hormones promote growth within plants. Plant hormones are unequally distributed throughout the stems and roots, which results in parts of the plant growing in a particular direction.','2022-04-28 21:37:57','2022-04-28 21:37:57'),(64,'Reproduction, the genome and genes',13,'Reproduction occurs in all organisms. DNA is important, as it allows new proteins to be synthesised. Mutations in the DNA can have serious implications.','2022-04-28 21:38:31','2022-04-28 21:38:31'),(65,'Genetic inheritance',13,'Our genes are inherited from our parents, and the different combinations of these genes make us unique. Genetic inheritance controls the characteristics of all living things.','2022-04-28 21:38:41','2022-04-28 21:38:41'),(66,'Variation',13,'Variation in species can be generated by genetics. Mutations arise spontaneously and can sometimes lead to genetic disorders or death. Genes can be inserted into a genome through genetic engineering.','2022-04-28 21:38:51','2022-04-28 21:38:51'),(67,'Evolution',13,'Evolution is the change of inherited characteristics within a population over time through natural selection, which may result in the formation of a new species.','2022-04-28 21:39:03','2022-04-28 21:39:03'),(68,'Classification of living organisms',13,'Living things are classified using a system developed by Carl Linnaeus. Organisms are commonly named by the binomial system of genus and species.','2022-04-28 21:39:15','2022-04-28 21:39:15'),(69,'Adaptations, interdependence,competition',14,'The abundance and distribution of organisms in an ecosystem is determined by biotic and abiotic factors. Animals and plants have adaptations to allow them to compete for resources.','2022-04-28 21:40:32','2022-04-28 21:40:32'),(70,'Organisation of an ecosystem',14,'The feeding relationships between organisms in an ecosystem can be seen in food chains. Sampling allows us to measure the abundance and distribution of these species.','2022-04-28 21:40:41','2022-04-28 21:40:41'),(71,'Decomposition',14,'Decomposition, or decay, is the breakdown of dead matter. The rate at which this happens depends upon the number of decomposing microorganisms, the temperature, and water and oxygen availability.','2022-04-28 21:40:50','2022-04-28 21:40:50'),(72,'Biodiversity and the effect of humans',14,'Biodiversity is a measure of how many different species live in an ecosystem. Human activities like changing land use, deforestation and peat bog destruction reduce this.','2022-04-28 21:41:05','2022-04-28 21:41:05'),(73,'Trophic levels in an ecosystem',14,'Feeding relationships are shown in food chains. Each stage is a trophic level. Biomass is a measure of the total mass of living material in each trophic level.','2022-04-28 21:41:17','2022-04-28 21:41:17'),(74,'Food production',14,'Factors such as the increase in human population, new pests and pathogens, overhunting and armed conflict, can result in food scarcity in some countries.','2022-04-28 21:41:25','2022-04-28 21:41:25'),(75,'The purpose and nature of businesses',25,'Entrepreneurs may choose to set up a business for a number of reasons and there are a number of business sectors that it can be in. To be successful, entrepreneurs need to have a number of characteristics.','2022-04-28 21:42:27','2022-04-28 21:42:27'),(76,'Business ownership',25,'There are a number of options for the ownership of a business. Each ownership type has its own advantages and disadvantages and a business should choose the one that best suits its needs.','2022-04-28 21:42:37','2022-04-28 21:42:37'),(77,'Setting business aims and objectives',25,'Businesses often set themselves targets that they want to achieve. These aims and objectives can be used to motivate employees and help a business measure their performance.','2022-04-28 21:42:46','2022-04-28 21:42:46'),(78,'Business stakeholders',25,'Businesses need to be aware of their stakeholders. The activities of a business will affect many of their stakeholders. The stakeholders can also influence the decisions that a business makes.','2022-04-28 21:42:54','2022-04-28 21:42:54'),(79,'Business location',25,'Business owners have to consider a number of things when choosing a location for their business. These include what type of business and how close they need to be to their customers, labour, materials and competitors.','2022-04-28 21:43:04','2022-04-28 21:43:04'),(80,'Business planning',25,'A business plan is an essential part of starting any business. Entrepreneurs create business plans to help them consider all of the elements they are going to need for their new business to be a success.','2022-04-28 21:43:12','2022-04-28 21:43:12'),(81,'Expanding a business',25,'As a business experiences success, it may begin to expand. There are several ways for a business to grow.','2022-04-28 21:43:24','2022-04-28 21:43:24'),(82,'Technology and business',26,'The speed at which technology advances is getting faster. Businesses need to be aware of the technology that is available to them, and how it might influence their sales, costs and marketing.','2022-04-28 21:43:41','2022-04-28 21:43:41'),(83,'Ethical and environmental considerations',26,'Businesses are increasingly judged on the contribution they make to society. Behaving ethically, without harming the environment, is an important part of this corporate social responsibility.','2022-04-28 21:43:51','2022-04-28 21:43:51'),(84,'The economy and business',26,'The economic climate has a big impact on businesses. The level of consumer spending affects prices, investment decisions and the number of workers that businesses employ.','2022-04-28 21:44:04','2022-04-28 21:44:04'),(85,'Business and globalisation',26,'In business, globalisation means operating on an international scale to provide or produce goods and services. Almost all of the goods we use are made of parts sourced from around the world.','2022-04-28 21:44:13','2022-04-28 21:44:13'),(86,'Legislation and business',26,'The government uses legislation to regulate businesses’ behaviour and prevent them from exploiting people. There are laws to protect consumers who buy from businesses and workers employed by businesses.','2022-04-28 21:44:24','2022-04-28 21:44:24'),(87,'Competitive environment',26,'The competitive environment relates to how a business is affected by its competition and how it adapts its businesses practices to enable it to compete effectively.','2022-04-28 21:44:32','2022-04-28 21:44:32'),(88,'Production processes',27,'A business must choose the right production method to suit its needs. They also have a choice between keeping surplus stock or using just-in-time stock control in order to meet customer demand.','2022-04-28 21:44:52','2022-04-28 21:44:52'),(89,'The role of procurement',27,'Procurement are responsible for the purchase and management of stock and supplies. Procurement have to decide which suppliers to use and hold a vital role in the supply chain.','2022-04-28 21:45:00','2022-04-28 21:45:00'),(90,'The concept of quality',27,'Quality is essential to a business’ success. Customers must be happy with the products and services they receive. If they are not, a business is unlikely to gain a good reputation or repeat customers.','2022-04-28 21:45:10','2022-04-28 21:45:10'),(91,'Good customer service',27,'Some businesses rely on good customer service to give them an advantage over their competitors. This can start before a customer has made a purchase and continue afterwards.','2022-04-28 21:45:19','2022-04-28 21:45:19'),(92,'Organisational structures',28,'Businesses use organisational structures to illustrate job roles and responsibilities. Organisational structures show who each employee reports to in their job.','2022-04-28 21:45:49','2022-04-28 21:45:49'),(93,'Recruitment and selection of employees',28,'One of the most important aspects of a business is its employees. Businesses must have good recruitment and selection techniques in place so that they find the best employees when they need them.','2022-04-28 21:46:01','2022-04-28 21:46:01'),(94,'Motivating employees',28,'Motivation determines how hard employees are willing to work for a business and how productive a business is. A business can motivate its employees through financial and non-financial methods.','2022-04-28 21:46:09','2022-04-28 21:46:09'),(95,'Training',28,'Businesses train their employees through a variety of methods to improve knowledge and enhance skills. This has many benefits for both the business and the employees.','2022-04-28 21:46:25','2022-04-28 21:46:25'),(96,'Identifying and understanding customer n',29,'Combining the elements of the marketing mix will help to inform the decisions that a business makes about its target market and the image it wants to convey.','2022-04-28 21:46:36','2022-04-28 21:46:36'),(97,'Combining the elements of the marketing',29,'Combining the elements of the marketing mix will help to inform the decisions that a business makes about its target market and the image it wants to convey.','2022-04-28 21:46:46','2022-04-28 21:46:46'),(98,'Sources of Finance',30,'Businesses need to consider how they will fund their activities when starting up as well as during their day-to-day operations. Various costs need to be covered, such as equipment, stock and paying bills.','2022-04-28 21:47:01','2022-04-28 21:47:01'),(99,'Business growth',30,'Business growth is important as it enables businesses to increase the scale of their operation and competitiveness. This may be done either internally (organically) or externally (inorganically).','2022-04-28 21:47:09','2022-04-28 21:47:09'),(100,'Cash and cash flow',30,'The management of cash and cash flow is important as it can prevent a business from failing. Cash flow is the way that money moves in and out of a business and its bank accounts.','2022-04-28 21:47:17','2022-04-28 21:47:17'),(101,'Financial terms and calculations',30,'Financial terms and calculations includes revenue, costs, profits and loss, average rate of return, and break-even. These financial elements inform key decisions in every business.','2022-04-28 21:47:25','2022-04-28 21:47:25'),(102,'Analysing financial performance',30,'Analysing financial performance in business is key to achieving success. Businesses use key financial statements to help them achieve this.','2022-04-28 21:47:40','2022-04-28 21:47:40'),(103,'Atoms, elements and compounds',16,'Chemists use symbols and formulae to represent elements and compounds. Word equations and balanced chemical equations represent the changes that happen in chemical reactions.','2022-04-28 21:48:19','2022-04-28 21:48:19'),(104,'Mixtures',16,'There are different ways to separate mixtures, such as filtration, crystallisation, simple distillation, fractional distillation and chromatography. The method chosen depends on the type of mixture.','2022-04-28 21:48:31','2022-04-28 21:48:31'),(105,'Atomic structure',16,'Atoms consist of a nucleus containing protons and neutrons, surrounded by electrons in shells. The number of subatomic particles in an atom can be calculated from the atom\'s atomic number and mass number.','2022-04-28 21:48:42','2022-04-28 21:48:42'),(106,'The periodic table',16,'Mendeleev made an early periodic table. In the modern periodic table, elements are in order of atomic number in periods and groups. Electronic structures model how electrons are arranged in atoms.','2022-04-28 21:48:51','2022-04-28 21:48:51'),(107,'Groups in the periodic table',16,'Elements in the same group of the periodic table show trends in physical properties, such as boiling point. They have the same number of electrons in their outer shell, so they are similar in their chemical properties.','2022-04-28 21:48:59','2022-04-28 21:48:59'),(108,'Transition metals',16,'The transition elements are metals. They have high melting points and densities, and are strong and hard. They form coloured compounds and act as catalysts.','2022-04-28 21:49:07','2022-04-28 21:49:07'),(109,'The three states of matter',17,'The three states of matter can be represented by the particle model. This model explains the properties of substances in their different states, as well as changes of state.','2022-04-28 21:49:23','2022-04-28 21:49:23'),(110,'Ionic compounds',17,'An ionic compound is made up of charged particles, called ions. It has a giant lattice structure with strong electrostatic forces of attraction.','2022-04-28 21:49:32','2022-04-28 21:49:32'),(111,'Small molecules',17,'A covalent bond is a shared pair of electrons. Covalent bonding forms molecules. Substances with small molecules have low melting and boiling points, and do not conduct electricity.','2022-04-28 21:49:45','2022-04-28 21:49:45'),(112,'Giant covalent molecules',17,'Giant covalent substances have many atoms joined together by covalent bonds. Diamond, graphite and graphene are forms of carbon with different giant covalent structures.','2022-04-28 21:50:05','2022-04-28 21:50:05'),(113,'Metals and alloys',17,'The structure of metals explains their high melting and boiling points and their conductivity. The properties of a metal can be modified by mixing it with another substance to form an alloy.','2022-04-28 21:50:12','2022-04-28 21:50:12'),(114,'Nanoscience',17,'Nanoparticles are 1 nm to 100 nm in size. They have very large surface area to volume ratios. The properties of nanoparticulate substances are different from those of the same substance in bulk.','2022-04-28 21:50:20','2022-04-28 21:50:20'),(115,'Calculations in chemistry',18,'Relative formula masses can be calculated and used in conservation of mass calculations. Calculations can be carried out to find out concentrations of solution and uncertainties in measurements.','2022-04-28 21:50:35','2022-04-28 21:50:35'),(116,'Calculations in chemistry (Higher)',18,'The mole is the unit for amount of substance. The number of particles in a substance can be found using the Avogadro constant. The mass of product depends upon the mass of limiting reactant.','2022-04-28 21:50:44','2022-04-28 21:50:44'),(117,'Atom economy, percentage yield and gases',18,'Percentage yield and atom economy show how much desired product is obtained compared to amounts of starting materials. Gas calculations show volumes of gas used and obtained in chemical reactions.','2022-04-28 21:51:03','2022-04-28 21:51:03'),(118,'Reactions of metals',19,'The reactivity series shows metals in order of reactivity. The reactivity of a metal is related to its tendency to form positive ions. Iron and aluminium are extracted from their ores in various ways.','2022-04-28 21:51:15','2022-04-28 21:51:15'),(119,'Acids, alkalis and salts',19,'Indicators are used to determine whether a solution is acidic or alkaline. Acids react with metals, bases and carbonates to produce salts. Neutralisation is the reaction between an acid and a base.','2022-04-28 21:51:23','2022-04-28 21:51:23'),(120,'Titrations',19,'The volumes of acids and alkali solutions that react with each other can be measured by titration using a suitable indicator.','2022-04-28 21:51:33','2022-04-28 21:51:33'),(121,'Electrolysis',19,'Electrolysis involves using electricity to break down electrolytes to form elements. The products of electrolysis can be predicted for a given electrolyte.','2022-04-28 21:51:42','2022-04-28 21:51:42'),(122,'Exothermic and endothermic reactions',20,'Exothermic reactions transfer energy to the surroundings and the temperature of the surroundings increases. Endothermic reactions take in energy and the temperature of the surroundings decreases.','2022-04-28 21:56:37','2022-04-28 21:56:37'),(123,'Chemical cells',20,'A chemical cell produces a voltage until one of the reactants is used up. In a hydrogen-oxygen fuel cell, hydrogen and oxygen are used to produce a voltage, and water is the only product.','2022-04-28 21:56:50','2022-04-28 21:56:50'),(124,'Rates of reaction',61,'The greater the frequency of successful collisions between reactant particles, the greater the reaction rate.','2022-04-28 21:57:03','2022-04-28 21:57:03'),(125,'Reversible reactions',61,'Chemical reactions are reversible and may reach a dynamic equilibrium. The position of equilibrium of a reversible reaction can be altered by changing the reaction conditions.','2022-04-28 21:57:15','2022-04-28 21:57:15'),(126,'Crude oil, hydrocarbons and alkanes',62,'Crude oil is a finite resource. Petrol and other fuels are produced from it using fractional distillation. Cracking is used to convert long alkanes into shorter, more useful hydrocarbons.','2022-04-28 21:57:27','2022-04-28 21:57:27'),(127,'More organic chemistry',62,'Alkanes, alkenes, alcohols and carboxylic acids are different homologous series of organic compounds. Naturally occurring and synthetic polymers can be formed from a variety of monomers.','2022-04-28 21:57:35','2022-04-28 21:57:35'),(128,'Analysing and identifying substances',63,'Formulations are complex mixtures of chemicals which have a specific use. Chromatography can be used to identify the substances present in a mixture of solutes.','2022-04-28 21:57:51','2022-04-28 21:57:51'),(129,'Analysing substances',63,'Flame tests and chemical tests are used to detect and identify ions in samples. Instrumental methods of analysis are faster, and more accurate and sensitive than simple chemical tests.','2022-04-28 21:58:01','2022-04-28 21:58:01'),(130,'Developing the atmosphere',64,'The early atmosphere was mainly carbon dioxide and water vapour. Water vapour condensed to form the oceans. Photosynthesis caused the amount of carbon dioxide to decrease and oxygen to increase.','2022-04-28 21:58:14','2022-04-28 21:58:14'),(131,'Polluting the atmosphere',64,'Human activities are causing global warming. Combustion of fuel produces many pollutants. Humans can reduce their impact on the environment.','2022-04-28 21:58:22','2022-04-28 21:58:22'),(132,'Sustainable development',65,'Many of the Earth’s resources are finite. Chemists have a role in estimating the amount of reserves remaining and ensuring that the use of resources is sustainable.','2022-04-28 21:58:35','2022-04-28 21:58:35'),(133,'Water',65,'All humans rely on safe drinking water. Salt can be removed from sea water to make it safe to drink. Waste water must be treated before being released into the environment.','2022-04-28 21:58:43','2022-04-28 21:58:43'),(134,'Ways of reducing the use of resources',65,'Life-cycle assessments can evaluate the environmental impact of a product. Many products are recycled to lessen environmental impact. Modern metal extraction can reduce the impact on the environment.','2022-04-28 21:58:52','2022-04-28 21:58:52'),(135,'Using materials',65,'Metals have many properties but some are prone to corrosion. Alloying metals improve their properties. Ceramics, polymers and composites have desirable properties that allows them specific uses.','2022-04-28 21:58:59','2022-04-28 21:58:59'),(136,'Fertilisers',65,'Fertilisers contain elements which are essential for the healthy growth of crops. Fertilisers can be made in the laboratory and on a larger scale by the chemical industry.','2022-04-28 21:59:07','2022-04-28 21:59:07'),(137,'States of matter',69,'Matter is made up of small particles called atoms. Atoms can exist on their own or together as molecules. Atoms are very small and around 100,000,000 of them end to end would measure one centimetre.','2022-04-28 22:29:03','2022-04-28 22:29:03'),(138,'Atomic structure - Synergy',69,'Atoms consist of a nucleus containing protons and neutrons, surrounded by electrons in shells. The numbers of subatomic particles in an atom can be calculated from its atomic number and mass number.','2022-04-28 22:29:34','2022-04-28 22:29:34'),(139,'Cells in animals and plants',69,'Organisms are made up of cells. Most organisms are multicellular and have cells that are specialised. Microscopes produce magnified images of cells.','2022-04-28 22:29:44','2022-04-28 22:29:44'),(140,'Transport into and out of cells',69,'For an organism to function, substances must move into and out of cells. Three processes contribute to this movement – diffusion, osmosis and active transport.','2022-04-28 22:29:53','2022-04-28 22:29:53'),(141,'Cell division - Synergy',69,'There are two types of cell division. Mitosis produces two identical diploid daughter cells. Meiosis produces four non-identical haploid gametes (sex cells).','2022-04-28 22:30:07','2022-04-28 22:30:07'),(142,'Waves',69,'Waves are one way in which energy may be transferred between stores. Both mechanical and electromagnetic waves will transfer energy without matter being transferred.','2022-04-28 22:30:17','2022-04-28 22:30:17'),(143,'Respiration - Synergy',70,'All living cells respire. This process releases the energy stored in glucose for life processes. Aerobic respiration occurs in the presence of oxygen, whilst anaerobic respiration occurs without it.','2022-04-28 22:30:43','2022-04-28 22:30:43'),(144,'Exchange surfaces and transport systems',70,'Most animals and plants consist of different types of cells organised as tissues, organs and systems. The human respiratory system is a body system adapted for efficient gas exchange.','2022-04-28 22:30:54','2022-04-28 22:30:54'),(145,'The digestive system',70,'The major nutrients required for a healthy diet are carbohydrates, proteins and lipids. The digestive system breaks down large molecules of food, which are then absorbed into the bloodstream.','2022-04-28 22:31:03','2022-04-28 22:31:03'),(146,'Coordination and control - Synergy',70,'The nervous system enables humans to react to their surroundings and to coordinate their behaviour. The endocrine system secretes hormones into the bloodstream from glands throughout the body.','2022-04-28 22:31:17','2022-04-28 22:31:17'),(147,'Plant organisation - Synergy',70,'Plant cells, tissues and organs are adapted to their functions. The stem, root and leaves form an organ system that transports substances into, around and out of a plant. The leaves are the main organ of photosynthesis.','2022-04-28 22:31:37','2022-04-28 22:31:37'),(148,'Photosynthesis - Synergy',70,'Plants use energy from sunlight to convert carbon dioxide and water into glucose and oxygen during photosynthesis.','2022-04-28 22:31:57','2022-04-28 22:31:57'),(149,'Plant diseases',70,'Plants can become infected with pathogens such as the tobacco mosaic virus and the rose black spot fungus.','2022-04-28 22:32:08','2022-04-28 22:32:08'),(150,'Lifestyle and health',71,'Health is the state of physical, mental and social well-being. It is not just being free from disease. Communicable diseases can be transferred from one person to another, whilst non-communicable diseases cannot.','2022-04-28 22:32:24','2022-04-28 22:32:24'),(151,'Homeostasis',71,'Homeostasis is the maintenance of a constant internal environment. Regulating body temperature, blood glucose level and water content are all examples of homeostasis.','2022-04-28 22:32:34','2022-04-28 22:32:34'),(152,'Reproduction and fertility',71,'Hormones are secreted by glands in the endocrine system. They are involved in puberty, regulating the menstrual cycle, contraception and fertility treatments.','2022-04-28 22:32:48','2022-04-28 22:32:48'),(153,'Radiation and risk',71,'There are many different types of radiation. Some are dangerous and some can be useful, it is important to understand the risks posed by all types of radiation.','2022-04-28 22:32:56','2022-04-28 22:32:56'),(154,'Preventing, treating and curing diseases',71,'Some diseases can be treated with antibiotics, but not all can be cured. Vaccinations allow protection against specific diseases, but the level of protection depends on the amount of people vaccinated.','2022-04-28 22:33:06','2022-04-28 22:33:06'),(155,'The atmosphere',72,'The early atmosphere was mainly carbon dioxide and water vapour. Human activities are releasing greenhouse gases which are causing global warming, and other atmospheric pollutants.','2022-04-28 22:33:18','2022-04-28 22:33:18'),(156,'Water - Synergy',72,'The water cycle describes how natural processes move water between living and non-living stores. All humans rely on safe drinking water. Water is purified to remove insoluble and soluble substances. Salt can be removed from sea water to make it safe to drink. Waste water must be treated before being released into the environment.','2022-04-28 22:33:40','2022-04-28 22:33:40'),(157,'Ecosystems and biodiversity',72,'An ecosystem is the living organisms in a particular area together with the non-living components of the environment, such as soil, air and water. An ecosystem is biodiverse if it contains many different species.','2022-04-28 23:38:38','2022-04-28 23:38:38'),(158,'Inheritance',72,'Inheritance is the process of passing genetic information to offspring. Genes are sections of DNA that code for a protein. Inheritance of genes can be shown in Punnett square diagrams.','2022-04-28 23:38:55','2022-04-28 23:38:55'),(159,'Evolution - Synergy',72,'Evolution is the change of inherited characteristics within a population over time through natural selection, which may result in the formation of a new species.','2022-04-28 23:39:14','2022-04-28 23:39:14'),(160,'The periodic table - Synergy',73,'Mendeleev made an early periodic table. In the modern periodic table, elements are in order of atomic number in periods and groups. Electronic structures model how electrons are arranged in atoms.','2022-04-28 23:39:54','2022-04-28 23:39:54'),(161,'Groups in the periodic table - Synergy',73,'Elements in the same group of the periodic table show trends in physical properties, such as boiling point. They have the same number of electrons in their outer shell, so they are similar in their chemical properties.','2022-04-28 23:40:24','2022-04-28 23:40:24'),(162,'Chemical equations',73,'Chemists use symbols and formulae to represent elements and compounds. Word equations and balanced chemical equations represent the changes that happen in chemical reactions.','2022-04-28 23:40:36','2022-04-28 23:40:36'),(163,'Calculations in chemistry - Synergy',73,'Relative formula masses can be calculated and used in conservation of mass calculations. Calculations can be carried out to find out concentrations of solutions.','2022-04-28 23:40:59','2022-04-28 23:40:59'),(164,'Forces',74,'Forces are responsible for all the interactions between particles and objects. They can be divided into two categories: contact forces and non-contact forces.','2022-04-28 23:42:52','2022-04-28 23:42:52'),(165,'Energy changes',74,'Energy is a key principle in physics. Forces cause changes and energy calculations allow us to measure how much change can happen.','2022-04-28 23:43:01','2022-04-28 23:43:01'),(166,'Ionic compounds - Synergy',74,'An ionic compound is made up of charged particles, called ions. It has a giant lattice structure with strong electrostatic forces of attraction.','2022-04-28 23:43:29','2022-04-28 23:43:29'),(167,'Covalent bonding',74,'A covalent bond is a shared pair of electrons. Covalent bonding results in the formation of molecules or giant structures. Substances with small molecules have low melting and boiling points and do not conduct electricity. Giant covalent substances have very high melting points.','2022-04-28 23:43:38','2022-04-28 23:43:38'),(168,'Metals',74,'Metals have giant structures of atoms with delocalised electrons. This explains their high melting and boiling points and why they conduct electricity.','2022-04-28 23:43:46','2022-04-28 23:43:46'),(169,'Magnetism and electromagnetism',74,'Magnetism is due to the magnetic fields around magnets. The fields can be investigated by looking at the effects of the forces they exert on other magnets and magnetic materials.','2022-04-28 23:43:56','2022-04-28 23:43:56'),(170,'Motion',75,'The movement of objects can be described using motion graphs and numerical values. These are both used to help in the design of faster and more efficient vehicles.','2022-04-28 23:44:14','2022-04-28 23:44:14'),(171,'Newton\'s laws',75,'Forces cause changes in the motion of an object. Newton’s Laws help us to understand and analyse those changes. Unbalanced forces cause changes in speed, shape or direction.','2022-04-28 23:44:21','2022-04-28 23:44:21'),(172,'Circuits',75,'Electrical current transfers energy around circuits. There are two types of current: direct and alternating.','2022-04-28 23:44:30','2022-04-28 23:44:30'),(173,'Mains electricity',75,'Electricity can flow either as direct or alternating current, and is used in homes to power electrical appliances. The National Grid distributes electricity throughout the country.','2022-04-28 23:44:39','2022-04-28 23:44:39'),(174,'Acids and alkalis',75,'Indicators are used to determine whether a solution is acidic or alkaline. Acids react in neutralisation reactions to produce salts.','2022-04-28 23:44:49','2022-04-28 23:44:49'),(175,'Rates of reaction - Synergy',75,'The greater the frequency of successful collisions between reactant particles, the greater the reaction rate. Temperature, concentration, pressure, particle size and the use of catalysts all affect reaction rate.','2022-04-28 23:45:12','2022-04-28 23:45:12'),(176,'Energy, rates and reactions',75,'Energy changes can be represented using energy profiles. Catalysts (including enzymes) speed up chemical reactions. Energy changes can be calculated from bond energies.','2022-04-28 23:45:23','2022-04-28 23:45:23'),(177,'Equilibria',75,'Some chemical reactions can be reversed. Reversible reactions can reach a dynamic equilibrium. Changing the conditions can change the amount of product made.','2022-04-28 23:45:33','2022-04-28 23:45:33'),(178,'Electrons and chemical reactions',75,'The reactivity series shows metals in order of reactivity. The reactivity of a metal is related to its tendency to form positive ions. Electrolysis can be used to split ionic compounds and to extract metals.','2022-04-28 23:45:47','2022-04-28 23:45:47'),(179,'Carbon chemistry',76,'Pure carbon can be found as diamond, graphite, fullerenes and graphene. Crude oil is made from hydrocarbons which can be processed to make a variety of fuels and other useful products.','2022-04-28 23:46:02','2022-04-28 23:46:02'),(180,'Material resources',76,'Metals and other useful resources can be extracted from the Earth\'s crust. Life cycle assessments measure the environmental impact of a product over its entire life. Recycling helps to conserve energy and resources.','2022-04-28 23:46:09','2022-04-28 23:46:09'),(181,'Energy resources',76,'Every person, animal and device transfers energy. Much of that energy is supplied by electricity, which must be generated from other energy stores. Some of these are renewable but most are non-renewable.','2022-04-28 23:46:15','2022-04-28 23:46:15'),(182,'Fundamentals of algorithms',66,'Algorithms are step-by-step plans for solving problems. They can be designed using pseudo-code and flowcharts.','2022-04-28 23:46:42','2022-04-28 23:46:42'),(183,'Common algorithms',66,'Sorting and searching are two of the most frequently needed algorithms in program design. Common algorithms have evolved to take account of this need.','2022-04-28 23:46:51','2022-04-28 23:46:51'),(184,'Programming constructs',66,'Programs are designed using common building blocks, known as programming constructs. These programming constructs form the basis for all programs.','2022-04-28 23:47:16','2022-04-28 23:47:16'),(185,'Programming techniques',66,'Proficient programming requires knowledge of many techniques. These techniques allow for powerful, complex programs to be created.','2022-04-28 23:47:31','2022-04-28 23:47:31'),(186,'Advanced programming techniques',66,'Proficient programming requires knowledge of many techniques. These techniques allow for powerful, complex programs.','2022-04-28 23:47:39','2022-04-28 23:47:39'),(187,'Types of programming language',66,'High-level languages allow programmers to write instructions in a language that is easier to understand than low-level languages. Translators are needed to translate programs written in high-level languages into the machine code that a computer understands.','2022-04-28 23:47:53','2022-04-28 23:47:53'),(188,'Fundamentals of data representation',66,'All data is represented as binary digits, whether it is numbers, text, images or sound. Calculations are also made in binary.','2022-04-28 23:48:07','2022-04-28 23:48:07'),(189,'Computer systems',67,'Computer systems are a combination of both hardware and software working together. Hardware is the physical components of a computer and software is the programs that run on a computer.','2022-04-28 23:48:17','2022-04-28 23:48:17'),(190,'Memory and storage',67,'Main memory is a key component of a computer system that works in tandem with secondary storage. This allows the system to run instructions, while secondary storage retains data. Cloud storage allows data to be stored at a remote location online.','2022-04-28 23:48:27','2022-04-28 23:48:27'),(191,'Computing fundamentals',67,'At the simplest level, computers are little more than a collection of transistors and circuits. They connect together to form logic gates, which in turn are used to form logic circuits.','2022-04-28 23:48:34','2022-04-28 23:48:34'),(192,'Fundamentals of computer networks',67,'Networking computers brings many benefits to users. Without networking, many computing applications would not be possible.','2022-04-28 23:48:43','2022-04-28 23:48:43'),(193,'Network topologies, protocols and layers',67,'Networks can be arranged in different topologies. Encryption is used to ensure that messages can be sent securely over a network.','2022-04-28 23:48:51','2022-04-28 23:48:51'),(194,'Fundamentals of cyber security',67,'Computer systems are at risk of intrusion, theft, and deletion. Cybercrime is evolving at the same rate as the technology around us.','2022-04-28 23:49:00','2022-04-28 23:49:00'),(195,'Ethical, legal and environmental impacts',67,'The use of computers has brought about ethical, legal and environmental impacts. These issues increasingly affect people\'s daily lives.','2022-04-28 23:49:16','2022-04-28 23:49:16'),(196,'New and emerging technologies',77,'Companies are trying to save money, improve products, develop new materials and become more efficient. New technologies are developed to positively impact the manufacturing industry and society.','2022-04-28 23:52:32','2022-04-28 23:52:32'),(197,'Energy generation and storage',77,'Energy generation and storage have a huge global impact on our lives - from decisions about the use of fossil fuels and their effect on our environment, to the development of cleaner, more-modern ways to create and store energy.','2022-04-28 23:52:42','2022-04-28 23:52:42'),(198,'Developments in new materials',77,'Developments in science and engineering lead to changes in materials technology. There are a range of modern materials with impressive properties, as well as traditional ones such as wood or metal.','2022-04-28 23:52:51','2022-04-28 23:52:51'),(199,'Systems approach to designing',77,'The systems approach to designing with programmable electronic devices is vital in understanding how today’s electronic devices are programmed together with how they operate in the real world.','2022-04-28 23:52:58','2022-04-28 23:52:58'),(200,'Mechanical devices',77,'Mechanical devices can change one form of force to another. All moving parts work on some sort of mechanism.','2022-04-28 23:53:05','2022-04-28 23:53:05'),(201,'Material categories and properties',77,'All materials have physical and working properties. Physical properties are the traits a material has before it is used, whereas working properties are how the material behaves when it is manipulated.','2022-04-28 23:53:12','2022-04-28 23:53:12'),(202,'Papers and boards',78,'Materials are chosen based on factors including working properties, aesthetics, environmental impact, function, manufacturing processes etc. It is important to choose a material fit for purpose.','2022-04-28 23:53:24','2022-04-28 23:53:24'),(203,'Timber-based materials',78,'Materials are chosen based on many factors including their working properties, aesthetics, environmental impact, function, manufacturing processes available etc. It is important to choose a material fit for purpose.','2022-04-28 23:53:31','2022-04-28 23:53:31'),(204,'Metal-based materials',78,'Materials are chosen based on factors including working properties, aesthetics, environmental impact, function, manufacturing processes etc. It is important to choose a material fit for purpose.','2022-04-28 23:53:42','2022-04-28 23:53:42'),(205,'Polymers',78,'Materials are chosen based on factors including working properties, aesthetics, environmental impact, function, manufacturing processes etc. It is important to choose a material fit for purpose.','2022-04-28 23:53:58','2022-04-28 23:53:58'),(206,'Textile-based materials',78,'Materials are chosen based on factors including working properties, aesthetics, environmental impact, function, manufacturing processes etc. It is important to choose a material fit for purpose.','2022-04-28 23:54:06','2022-04-28 23:54:06'),(207,'Electronic and mechanical systems',78,'Components are chosen based on factors including working properties, environmental impact, function, manufacturing processes etc. It is important to choose a component fit for purpose.','2022-04-28 23:54:13','2022-04-28 23:54:13'),(208,'Investigating',79,'During the designing and making processes it is important to gather feedback from the client and users. Refining the product based on this feedback helps solve any problems before production begins.','2022-04-28 23:54:25','2022-04-28 23:54:25'),(209,'Designing',79,'Designers use many techniques to create products and solve problems. Design and development involve creating working drawings and parts lists to enable a third party to manufacture the design.','2022-04-28 23:54:33','2022-04-28 23:54:33'),(210,'Making',79,'Manufacturers need to consider the form, function and cost of designs before production. Designers need to consider safety, availability of materials and minimising waste, while maintaining quality.','2022-04-28 23:54:41','2022-04-28 23:54:41'),(211,'Evaluating',79,'Evaluating ideas, models and feedback is an ongoing process, utilised in continuing to adapt and improve products to make them more useful, appealing and profitable.','2022-04-28 23:54:49','2022-04-28 23:54:49'),(212,'Digital data - CCEA',80,'What is digital data? How is it represented, stored and shared?','2022-04-29 00:00:06','2022-04-29 00:00:06'),(213,'System software - CCEA',80,'The functions of system software and their modes of processing, tasks carried out by utility applications, the role of antivirus software and the importance of regular system updates.','2022-04-29 00:00:13','2022-04-29 00:00:13'),(214,'Database applications - CCEA',80,'Databases are at the heart of digital technology, making data easy to store, organise and search.','2022-04-29 00:00:25','2022-04-29 00:00:25'),(215,'Spreadsheet applications - CCEA',80,'Spreadsheets can help you calculate values from data using various formulae. They can also be used for data modelling and the visual representation of data.','2022-04-29 00:00:32','2022-04-29 00:00:32'),(216,'Hardware and network technologies - CCEA',80,'Hardware is the physical components of a computer system. When we connect computers together to share data, software and hardware we create a network.','2022-04-29 00:00:40','2022-04-29 00:00:40'),(217,'Cyberspace, network security and data',80,'Networks make computers more powerful, but also more vulnerable to attack. In the era of the internet and cloud computing, what are the threats to data security?','2022-04-29 00:00:52','2022-04-29 00:00:52'),(218,'Ethical, legal and environmental impact',80,'How does life, society and the law react to the evolution of digital technology?','2022-04-29 00:01:04','2022-04-29 00:01:04'),(219,'Digital applications - CCEA',80,'The advent of digital technology has radically affected our lives, but what are the positive and negative aspects of those changes?','2022-04-29 00:01:11','2022-04-29 00:01:11'),(220,'Designing solutions - CCEA',81,'Software designers must produce specifications to guide development teams, then they must test the software.','2022-04-29 00:01:24','2022-04-29 00:01:24'),(222,'Digital development considerations',81,'Accessibility and operability across different interfaces are crucial to the development of a successful digital product.','2022-04-29 00:02:15','2022-04-29 00:02:15'),(223,'Multimedia applications - CCEA',81,'Multimedia applications combine elements like text, images, audio and video and require specific considerations in their design.','2022-04-29 00:02:24','2022-04-29 00:02:24'),(224,'Database development - CCEA',81,'Developing the right type and structure of database allows you to store, access, search and output your data to your greatest advantage.','2022-04-29 00:02:32','2022-04-29 00:02:32'),(225,'Testing - CCEA',81,'Software testing involves testing a program under various conditions to make sure it works. Even the best programmers make mistakes, so it is important that these are identified as soon as possible in the development stage so that errors can be fixed.','2022-04-29 00:02:40','2022-04-29 00:02:40'),(226,'Evaluation - CCEA',81,'How is a product evaluated and user tested, and why? Evaluation and user testing help ensure products meet their original design specification, offer an efficient solution, operate across appropriate platforms and are full and complete.','2022-04-29 00:02:49','2022-04-29 00:02:49'),(227,'Designing solutions with the right tools',82,'When creating a digital solution for an end user, you must establish the user requirements and create, evaluate and refine clear design plans.','2022-04-29 00:03:18','2022-04-29 00:03:18'),(228,'Building a solution - CCEA',82,'Once you have designed your solution, you must code your Controlled Assessment website using Hypertext Markup Language (HTML).','2022-04-29 00:03:27','2022-04-29 00:03:27'),(229,'Testing a solution - CCEA',82,'You must produce a robust test plan for both your website and database solution. Testing should use appropriate test data and be evidenced with screenshots.','2022-04-29 00:03:39','2022-04-29 00:03:39'),(230,'Trends in software development',83,'Software development and programming paradigms change over time, from imperative programming to high level languages like Python and C++.','2022-04-29 00:04:07','2022-04-29 00:04:07'),(231,'Digital data',83,'What is digital data, and how do computers understand it? How is digital data represented, stored, shared and manipulated?','2022-04-29 00:04:41','2022-04-29 00:04:41'),(232,'Digital design principles - CCEA',83,'Digital design demands an understanding of computational thinking, as programming simply tells a computer what to do and how to do it.','2022-04-29 00:04:52','2022-04-29 00:04:52'),(233,'Programming constructs - CCEA',83,'Computer programs use data stores to organise the different types of data they contain. Data stores can be either a constant, variable or an array, and contain inputs, outputs, functions, instructions, sequences and more.','2022-04-29 00:05:01','2022-04-29 00:05:01'),(234,'Programming constructs concepts',83,'Computer programs use data stores to organise the different types of data they contain. Data stores can be either a constant, variable or an array, and contain inputs, outputs, functions, instructions, sequences and more.','2022-04-29 00:05:52','2022-04-29 00:05:52'),(235,'Simple error handling techniques - CCEA',83,'In some ways, computer languages are no different to our own. They have strict rules programmers must follow in order to make their programs understood. Mistakes throw up errors, which must be fixed.','2022-04-29 00:06:01','2022-04-29 00:06:01'),(236,'Developing and testing a solution',83,'Once software has been created, it must be tested under different conditions to make sure it works. This can be achieved with white box, black box, unit, integration and system testing, as well as thorough planning and evaluation.','2022-04-29 00:06:23','2022-04-29 00:06:23'),(237,'Designing solutions',84,'In this unit, students design, develop and test coded solutions when creating digital systems. Students must use one of the following languages in their completed solution: Python, Java or C#.','2022-04-29 00:06:49','2022-04-29 00:06:49'),(238,'Building a solution',84,'Building a solution involves coding in an appropriate high level language, choosing an appropriate Integrated Development Environment (IDE), testing and documenting its development.','2022-04-29 00:07:00','2022-04-29 00:07:00'),(239,'Testing a solution',84,'Once the development stage is complete you must complete integration, system and acceptance testing on your code and evaluate your solution.','2022-04-29 00:07:09','2022-04-29 00:07:09'),(240,'Theatre roles',85,'Theatre is a collaborative art form, with lots of people working together to move a play from page to stage.','2022-04-29 00:08:28','2022-04-29 00:08:28'),(241,'Characteristics of a dramatic work',85,'It is important to understand the characteristics of a dramatic work to make sense of it.','2022-04-29 00:08:38','2022-04-29 00:08:38'),(242,'Staging',85,'The way that a performance space is arranged will impact how a show is staged and performed.','2022-04-29 00:08:45','2022-04-29 00:08:45'),(243,'Stage positioning',85,'Stage positions are used to help keep track of how performers and set pieces move during rehearsal and performance.','2022-04-29 00:08:53','2022-04-29 00:08:53'),(244,'Physical skills for interpreting a chara',86,'Performers use a range of physical skills to portray a character. Their physical choices can also convey the character’s feelings.','2022-04-29 00:09:26','2022-04-29 00:09:26'),(245,'Vocal interpretation of a character',86,'Performers use a range of vocal skills to create characters and express how those characters are feeling.','2022-04-29 00:09:35','2022-04-29 00:09:35'),(246,'Set design',87,'The set is the space where the performance takes place and is crucial in helping to convey the setting.','2022-04-29 00:10:37','2022-04-29 00:10:37'),(247,'Costume design',87,'A costume is what a performer wears on stage. Everything the performer wears, including wigs and make-up, has to be carefully considered by a costume designer.','2022-04-29 00:10:44','2022-04-29 00:10:44'),(248,'Lighting design',87,'Lighting design is an important aspect of theatre design that helps to create meaning, mood and atmosphere on stage.','2022-04-29 00:10:50','2022-04-29 00:10:50'),(249,'Sound design',87,'Sound and music are used in theatre to convey meaning and atmosphere. Technical aspects need to be considered, as well as the selection of appropriate sources.','2022-04-29 00:11:02','2022-04-29 00:11:02'),(250,'Puppet design',87,'A puppet is an object that is animated by a puppeteer to resemble a character within a performance.','2022-04-29 00:11:10','2022-04-29 00:11:10'),(251,'Responding to a stimulus',88,'There are different dramatic techniques that can be included in a practical piece of work, including both vocal and physical elements, to help to bring a stimulus to life.','2022-04-29 00:12:08','2022-04-29 00:12:08'),(252,'Developing an idea',88,'It is vital to employ a range of exploratory techniques to develop and work on initial ideas for a devised piece.','2022-04-29 00:12:21','2022-04-29 00:12:21'),(253,'Selecting a genre or performance style',88,'There are many genres and styles that can be explored in the initial stages of a devised piece to develop and steer it. It is vital that the chosen genre or style will work for the target audience.','2022-04-29 00:12:28','2022-04-29 00:12:28'),(254,'Selecting a practitioner',88,'Different theatre practitioners use various methods for performance and design and these can be used as an influence when creating a piece of theatre.','2022-04-29 00:12:35','2022-04-29 00:12:35'),(255,'Rehearsing for a performance',88,'There are several stages within the rehearsal process to refine both design and performance elements.','2022-04-29 00:12:42','2022-04-29 00:12:42'),(256,'Refining a performance',88,'There are many ways that a performance can be refined and developed by both performers and designers.','2022-04-29 00:12:49','2022-04-29 00:12:49'),(257,'Interpreting and performing a character',88,'There are several tools available to performers when interpreting and performing a character, all of which can be experimented with.','2022-04-29 00:12:58','2022-04-29 00:12:58'),(258,'Designing a production',88,'There are several different designers working within each production. Each is responsible for communicating meaning to an audience through their designs on stage in a variety of ways.','2022-04-29 00:13:05','2022-04-29 00:13:05'),(259,'Health and safety considerations',88,'Being aware of health and safety requirements is essential for performers and designers when creating and performing drama, to prevent injury.','2022-04-29 00:13:12','2022-04-29 00:13:12'),(260,'Creating a portfolio or devising log',88,'Creating a portfolio or devising log is a creative and developmental process. The end result documents the procedure of devising a piece of drama.','2022-04-29 00:13:18','2022-04-29 00:13:18'),(261,'Features of a script',89,'Playwrights use the features of scripts to communicate to directors, performers and designers how to bring the play to life and take it from page to stage.','2022-04-29 00:13:59','2022-04-29 00:13:59'),(262,'Performing a script',89,'Performers aim to communicate a script effectively, using various acting skills to engage the audience and sustain their interest throughout a performance.','2022-04-29 00:14:05','2022-04-29 00:14:05'),(263,'Designing for a scripted performance',89,'Designers need to create a design that contributes to the overall effect of the performance and communicates its intended meaning to the audience.','2022-04-29 00:14:13','2022-04-29 00:14:13'),(264,'How to answer set text exam questions',90,'The written exam contains questions on a set text studied during the course, to test knowledge and understanding of how drama is developed and performed.','2022-04-29 00:15:06','2022-04-29 00:15:06'),(265,'Live theatre evaluation',90,'Live theatre evaluation involves analysing and evaluating a piece of theatre while demonstrating knowledge and understanding of how theatre is performed.','2022-04-29 00:15:13','2022-04-29 00:15:13'),(266,'Non-fiction text types',2,'Non-fiction texts come in many types, and have many different purposes. They surround us in everyday life but can also come in more sophisticated forms.','2022-04-29 00:15:38','2022-04-29 00:15:38'),(267,'Purpose and audience',2,'When we talk about the purpose of a text, we are talking about what the writer wants to achieve. Writers use language and structural features to deliberately appeal to their intended audience.','2022-04-29 00:15:45','2022-04-29 00:15:45'),(268,'Language and structure - Non-Fiction',2,'Writers choose words and language features deliberately - to have an effect on their readers. The way they structure parts of a text, eg openings and endings, influences the reader too.','2022-04-29 00:16:13','2022-04-29 00:16:13'),(269,'Responding to a non-fiction text',2,'In the exams, you will demonstrate your understanding of non-fiction text types, their intended audience and purpose, and how the writer has used language and structure.','2022-04-29 00:16:22','2022-04-29 00:16:22'),(270,'How to compare texts',3,'Comparing involves directly linking texts through their similarities and differences. It is important to move equally between the two texts, and write about them together, not separately.','2022-04-29 00:16:37','2022-04-29 00:16:37'),(271,'Audience, purpose and form',4,'Establishing audience, purpose and form allows you to choose the most appropriate language, tone and structure.','2022-04-29 00:16:53','2022-04-29 00:16:53'),(272,'Writing fiction',4,'Writing fiction is an opportunity to come up with creative and original ways of using language. You might find inspiration from your own experiences or from your imagination.','2022-04-29 00:17:00','2022-04-29 00:17:00'),(273,'Writing non-fiction',4,'Non-fiction texts are those that deal with facts, opinions and the real world. Many non-fiction texts follow specific conventions of language and structure.','2022-04-29 00:17:06','2022-04-29 00:17:06'),(274,'Planning',4,'It’s always a good idea to plan before you write. You can gather your main ideas, list vocabulary you’d like to include and map out your structure in a way that makes writing easier.','2022-04-29 00:17:13','2022-04-29 00:17:13'),(275,'Organising information and ideas',4,'Well-organised writing is easy to follow and understand. Points follow on from and build upon each other to lead to clear conclusions.','2022-04-29 00:17:19','2022-04-29 00:17:19'),(276,'Using language effectively',4,'Writers use language to create different effects. Learning how to use these will make your writing more engaging.','2022-04-29 00:17:26','2022-04-29 00:17:26'),(277,'Vocabulary',4,'Make your writing interesting and lively by using a wide range of vocabulary. Use specific words to convey your meaning.','2022-04-29 00:17:35','2022-04-29 00:17:35'),(278,'Spelling',5,'Learning to spell correctly means you’re more likely to be understood. You can improve your confidence by reading widely and learning to use spelling strategies.','2022-04-29 00:17:48','2022-04-29 00:17:48'),(279,'Punctuation',5,'Using punctuation effectively means that your reader can make sense of your writing. It can also help create dramatic effects in your writing.','2022-04-29 00:17:55','2022-04-29 00:17:55'),(280,'Grammar',5,'Grammar refers to the structure of language and how different words fit together. Knowing something about English grammar rules should help you to construct clear and meaningful sentences.','2022-04-29 00:18:05','2022-04-29 00:18:05'),(281,'Speaking and listening',6,'Effective face-to-face communication means thinking about audience and purpose. Generally this means using Standard English, listening carefully and being polite and co-operative.','2022-04-29 00:18:25','2022-04-29 00:18:25'),(282,'Personal presence',6,'Face-to-face communication includes the words you say and, more importantly, the way you say them. Eye-contact, gesture and posture can all add to the impact of your talk.','2022-04-29 00:18:34','2022-04-29 00:18:34'),(283,'Voice',6,'How you speak affects the meaning of your words. Varying your tone, volume and pace can help engage a listener.','2022-04-29 00:18:44','2022-04-29 00:18:44'),(284,'Individual researched presentation',6,'In an individual researched presentation you will need to give a presentation in front of an audience. You’ll need to research your topic beforehand and may need to answer questions from the audience.','2022-04-29 00:18:51','2022-04-29 00:18:51'),(285,'Responding and interacting',6,'Participating in a group discussion allows you to respond and interact with others. You can share your opinion as well as respond to the opinion of others.','2022-04-29 00:18:58','2022-04-29 00:18:58');
